overview: The user initiated a request to evaluate an existing sleep
  questionnaire codebase against a Statement of Work. The primary goal was to
  integrate a database for storing questionnaire responses and develop a simple
  admin dashboard for data access and CSV export. After an initial codebase
  review, it was determined that a database model for responses, API routes for
  data handling, an authentication system, and an admin dashboard were missing.
  Key decisions included using NeonDB (PostgreSQL) for the database,
  implementing a simple password-based authentication via environment variables,
  and updating the demographic data collected to include year of birth, sex, zip
  code, weight, and height. The plan was then created, and the initial
  implementation steps of updating the demographic fields in the application's
  types, validation schemas, and form components, along with defining the
   model in the Prisma schema, have been successfully
  completed.
